    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Taken from <a href=\"http://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/util/Calendar.html#add%28int,%20int%29\" rel=\"noreferrer\">the docs here</a>: </p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>Adds or subtracts the specified amount of time to the given calendar field, based on the calendar's rules. For example, to subtract 5 days from the current time of the calendar, you can achieve it by calling:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Calendar calendar = Calendar.getInstance(); // this would default to now\ncalendar.add(Calendar.DAY_OF_MONTH, -5).\n</code></pre>\n</blockquote>\n"
