    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Instead of writing my own <code>addDays</code> as suggested by Eli, I would prefer to use <code>DateUtils</code> from <strong>Apache</strong>. It is handy especially when you have to use it multiple places in your project.</p>\n\n<p>The API says: </p>\n\n<p><code>addDays(Date date, int amount)</code> </p>\n\n<p>Adds a number of days to a date returning a new object.</p>\n\n<p>Note that it returns a new <code>Date</code> object and does not make changes to the previous one itself. </p>\n"
